      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six power plant. This example has undergone critical preventative maintenance, including a comprehensive VANOS system overhaul and documented rear subframe reinforcement to ensure chassis integrity. Power is delivered through a precise 6-speed manual gearbox to a factory limited-slip differential, providing exceptional mechanical grip. The suspension remains taut with refreshed bushings and dampers, maintaining the platform's signature telepathic turn-in. While showing minor cosmetic patina expected of its age, the drivetrain is robust, exhibiting linear power delivery and a healthy redline. A mechanically honest machine for the serious enthusiast.",
